text:
i know the intention is well meaning, and i am by no means looking for any apologies. but i am growing tired of hearing, â€œyouâ€™re lucky you didnâ€™t get married. youâ€™re lucky you donâ€™t share a child. youâ€™re lucky you got out as soon as you did.â€
.
like most survivors of emotional and psychological abuse, i am sensitive to language. (communication was my abuserâ€™s weapon of choice after all.) and the word, â€œluckyâ€ just doesnâ€™t sit well with me in this context. there was nothing lucky about what i experienced. could it have been worse? i donâ€™t know. itâ€™s impossible for me to imagine worse.
.
to call me lucky invalidates my trauma. it makes trauma a competition, when it is anything but.
.

text:
i look like hell today. for the last 15 years ive had nightmares of an abuser who i know to be dead. sexual assault sucks and the ptsd that comes after is real. i was in emdr therapy but it got too expsensive so i stopped going. the dreams had seemed to have stopped so i didnt think anything of stopping therapy. i was mistaken. the dreams have come back and idk why. my kids are what pushes me through the day. today is already at a rough start itll probably be a rough day but ill make it through because i have to. i didnt want to get out of bed but i made myself. im a surviver and i wont let this stop me. i just wish i knew what triggers the nightmares.
#ptsdisreal 
#sexualassaultisnojoke 
#metoo

text:
071018 part 2.
...after a very short waiting time, his mother knocked on my door saying the police is there looking for me. i told her to tell them to come upstairs. i wasnt going to open the door to her. god knows what they will do to me. so the police called my name and i opened the door. i told the female officer what happened before they came and she said we will wait for you no matter how long if you can call your friend to pick you up. dont worry she said. the male officer assured me with a nod. he went downstairs and my husband's mother was talking to the officer. i could hear her talk to him. she was completely unempathic like his son. that moment the female officer was guarding my room while i pack my stuff. it was funny that, that moment was a revelation to me: the reason why my husband is the way he is has always been because of his mother. exactly the same personality. no empathy and manipulative. i packed my stuff and told the officer it would be easier to take uber. so i packed only what sofia and i needed. i was shaking in anger for what suddenly has dawned on me. i saw what i needed to see. finally, i packed everything and the officer told me she will carry it for me. i told her they are too heavy and she told me to trust her because she lifts anything way bigger. i said okay. she took all my stuff downstairs and the male officer made sure that as i walk out of the house that nobody was there to stop me. i of course only took sofia with me while the driver and the officers helped me and the male officer secured sofia's seat because the carseat base wasnt available in the car. i left my baby's stroller and most of her stuff. my husband's mother was trying to desuade the officer to not let me take sofia and she was asking for an address where im taking my baby. i said i will text her son. the officer said "she can take her child with her whenever she wants because it's her baby". the officers escorted me out as my husband's mother was glaring at me like a psychopath. she was acting so calm with a smile on her face. btw, i have more to tell you about how they've been acting  at home... to be continued...

text:
07102018 part 3
when my ex husband's family came in august everything went downhill. everytime from 2015, 2016, to 2018 when they come together everything becomes really difficult for me. my ex becomes very abusive. he intimidates me & even tries to advance towards me as if he was going to hurt me. let me begin here. they came at almost midnight in august 17 need to check the date. i was so tired because i was with the baby the whole day without help. my ex wouldnt hire help. he said i should pay for it. i was on my 7th week of recovery postpartum. he also wouldnt buy a changing table because he loves to save money even if its to help me recover. i had to bend down everytime when changing the baby because the bed is lower than a changing table. my back was hurting so bad. when they finally came from the airport i was dead tired. sofia was in my arms because she wakes up when i put her down on the bed. i didnt know that time that i already violated his customs in serbia. later on in one of our repetitive email converstaions (we dont talk in person, its impossoble!), he actually expected me to be at the door welcoming his family to our home. seriously? after having no sleep since i pushed the baby out he expects this from me?! and he reiterates that i did not bring the baby down with me. i did! the guy is either having amnesia or just really mental. my ex put sofia on the corner in her cradle. his sister immediately asked me if i usually leave the baby there the whole night. my mind was in awe by such a question. who does that? a newborn left in a cradle/rocker the whole night? she asked if sofia has her own crib? i said yes she has. i really thought things got lost in translation because as my ex always says "english is not our first language" everytime he is confronted with the truth. somehow her question made me realize that between them there is also lack of communication. for how much they can talk they actually do not communicate!ğŸ˜… how can they not know that they will be sleeping in my baby's room? if my ex told them his sister would know if sofia has a room then she must have a crib! babies dont sleep on the floor! to be continued...

text:
07102018 part 5. 
i was told not post this but for all of us women who are experiencing domestic violence this is for you! #domesticviolence
...so his sister left my room finally & decided to go to chicago for many days. meanwhile my neighbors' mom just came for a visit for 6 months and since i met her she's been giving me soups almost everyday. my ex knows its part of our culture to give food to new moms. we dont let them work until they have recovered! the neighbors have been giving me food eversince but all of a sudden, my husband is pissed that i receive food from them?!!! he opened the door and told the neighbor to stop giving me food & instead to give me the recipe so i can make it at home. "we have food here at home" he said. i was so embarassed. instead of saying thank you he reprimanded the old woman. i apologized immediately. you see when your parents didnt teach you good moral values? or growing up in hatred and atheism? he has hit me more than 3 times in a span of four years. once with a towel, a shirt, then his big hand landed on my left ear with a big ringing sound. i wanted to call the police but i didnt want to hurt his immigration status. truth be told i'm his 3rd wife. for a 35 year old man who has been married 3 times and who constantly blames his partners for being bipolar? now i know why, because my ex tells me everytime that i'm crazy! now i dont believe him for having his own diagnoses of his ex wife. im sure she wasnt bipolar but that my ex was at fault in those marriages. he is not capable of empathy, sympathy, he is very impulsive, angry, he puts you down everytime, he calls you names, he lies to get out of trouble, doesnt admit his mistakes no matter what, he doesnt even see his faults. he cannot see parallelism in situations, and he needed help with his studies for 1 year and 6 months---i was helping him all the time bringing his projects at my work and then coming home running straight to the kitchen to make dinner. i used to carry 30 kilos of clothes to the basement to wash all his clothes. he wouldnt let me wash until the laundry is overflowing because he wants to save some quarters! he took $4500 from me 4 years ago...tbcont...

...to pay for my share that i didnt pay for 9 months of not working. afterall i was doing for him he wanted money! i couldnt enroll in school and couldnt pursue my phd due to having little to no money but he couldnt wait until i was settled. aside from that he started saying foul words "fu** you", calls me "b****", "w****", and many other unthinkable words and names. if this is normal in their family, it's not with mine! esp. given the fact that he was only my second boyfriend. i dont party, i dont smoke, i dont drink any type of alcoholic drinks either; the guy is mental! once i wanted to go out because he doesnt take me out at all especially in the first 3 years, i wanted to see the cherry blossoms festival two years ago but knowing how impatient and unforgiving he is he was angry  the whole time because of the traffic. he was angry with me too because i wanted something "difficult" even if it was a free event; my ex would never pay a penny if he could avoid it.
...going back to august and october event: he was expecting me to have breakfast, lunch & dinner with his family after all that has happened in the first 48 hours of their arrival. i wouldnt. 1.nobody apoligized 2.nobody was helping me 3.he comes angry into the room and when i talk back he advances toward me so i tell him i will call the police 4.he tells his family how inadequate i am 5.he became even more aggressive in action & in speech 6.there were days in august when he didnt even look at sofia 7.they take sofia out on a 90 degrees heat (so hot his dad fell on the ground!) 8.sofia came home with a scraped thigh which he said my nails caused 9.his mother takes sofia out on a rainy day 10.he defends his mother and sister instead of apologizing for their mistakes 11.sofia constantly misses her feedings at 7 weeks of age when they take her with them 12.they wont give her back to me until 10:30 pm 13. he was shaking sofia when she's crying!!! 14.he burps her by squeezing her until she is gasping for breath 15.he doesnt change her diaper for hours when they take her from me 16.he feeds her with the bottle upright and her head tilted upwards in a very dangerous choking hazard position...tbc...

repost @atikaa_ahluwalia

i was attacked by a man i was in a significant relationship with. pushed, thrown on the ground, kicked, held in a chokehold, different things on different days. in all my life before that, i never imagined myself as someone who could be physically abused. i mean, i'm educated, outspoken and independent. i travel the world and read vogue magazine. stuff like this just couldnâ€™t happen to me. right? 
wrong. and how. it started with the shouting and the pushing. then came the things (including the breakfast i'd just made) that would be sent flying across the room. my cell phone would be taken away. messages from my family erased before i could see them. a couple of months into the relationship, i found myself on the floor one day, my tail bone hurting because i had just been kicked. in that one moment on the floor i remember thinking â€“ iâ€™ve read about this kind of thing in agony aunt columns. is this what they call physical abuse? no, no, no. thatâ€™s for those financially dependent, meek types that have had the misfortune of marrying big, mean looking men. this canâ€™t be that. even though i had a ominous feeling that something was incredibly wrong, i told myself it's going to be okay tomorrow. 
it never really did. one day, i decided that i had had enough. i was leaving. thatâ€™s when i was held in a chokehold against the wall and told to â€˜try and leave nowâ€™. the funny thing is. i still didnâ€™t. i stayed another 90 days. after all, i â€˜lovedâ€™ him. and believed that he â€˜lovedâ€™ me in his own twisted way too. 
the picture you see above is me today. on my unique life journey and blissfully abuse-free. 
i left my abuser years ago and the day i did, i began a new, wonderful, painful, spiritual and magical journey that was possible because of the one thing that iâ€™d like to share with all of you. hope.

text:
my ptsd has been in overdrive these past few weeks. 
the global conversation around sexual assault is so important, but itâ€™s survivors who suffer most from that conversation. 
i keep thinking things are calming down (for me, anyhow) 
but then something will happen and iâ€™m suddenly feeling not safe and angry and shaky and nauseous and all the things that come with the way my ptsd manifests. 
iâ€™ve been down on myself about it lately, for not pulling through this patch better or sooner or whatever other self-blaming nonsense also accompanies ptsd. 
but then, this morning, a friend got really honest about how their post-kavanaugh flare up is still affecting them, and i instantly felt so much less alone. 
so, i decided to write this today, in case you too are feeling stuck and down on yourself, and needed a reminder that:
â€¢ you didnâ€™t choose this
â€¢ you donâ€™t get to choose how youâ€™re triggered, how your body responds to those triggers, or how long their effects will last â€¢ now is a time to be kind to yourself, meet your physical needs, so your body feels safe, and surround yourself with situations and people who make you feel safe. 
youâ€™re a warrior. 
youâ€™ve made it this far. 
keep fighting. 
it wonâ€™t always be this hard. â€¢

text:
those against #metoo often point out 2 â€˜flawsâ€™ in the movement.

the claims shared are treated without question. no one asks, â€œhey, is this really true?â€ or questions the reliability of the story. those who then never truly committed the crime, but were claimed as having done otherwise, would become victims of both circumstance and witch hunts because no one bothered to fact check or hear the other side of the story. 
the movement fusses over actions that are, at most, annoying flirting. due to the possible consequences that can be faced for sexual misconduct, some argue that several of the stories are blown out of proportion and the actions of the individual involved were simply flirting that was, at the worst, persistent. however, never harmful. mainly, flirting should never land someone 4 years in jail (at the least). (2)

text:
after spending a crisp fall yesterday out on the campaign trail, i took an hour to grocery shop (seriously love this task) and then go home for dinner with (some of) the family. i roasted a chicken & baked a cake to show my family,who have been supporting me through this hectic campaign season, that i love them deeply. 
last night was also the nh state democratic partyâ€™s â€œeleanor roosevelt dinnerâ€ which i had been so very excited to attend, until the planning committee choose alec baldwin as the keynote speaker. immediately i knew i was out. while he does an amusing comedic interpretation of our president, his long sordid history of abuse of his daughter, dismissal of the seriousness of the #metoo survivors, mocking sexual harassment and reflexive racism & homophobia in times of stress are disqualifiers for me to buy a ticket to this event. this was a great disappointment to me, not having the opportunity to spend time with some people i truly admire & respect but alec baldwin was more than a guest i could steer clear of at a party, he was the headliner on the program. i am disappointed in the planners who choose this divisive man to sell tickets in the first year this annual event is finally named for a woman. i sincerely hope better choices are made next year. #nhpolitics
name: Debra Altschiller

text:
former miss universe sushmita sen is proud of the women who have spoken up about their unsavoury experiences, as a result of the metoo movement. she says now is the time to listen, believe and let justice prevail.

sushmita interacted with the media at the bombay times fashion week here on sunday.

she said she doesn't find the revelations coming up in context of the metoo movement shocking at all as people were aware of these things for long. "it is going to be shocking every single time, but we are also not ignorant people. it's not like we didn't know these things were happening in india and in the world. i think what is more shocking that we did not listen to it for so long and that we didn't do anything about it. this is the start, and you have to listen, believe and let justice prevail," sushmita said.

text:

if we as a nation keep going like this, our 6 year old daughter or son could be the next "victim" just because one child tried to squeeze past the other child in the lunch line and something accidentally touched.

and it's not just this movement, have u watched the news lately? smdh. it breaks my heart that my 3 girls are going to have to grow up in this world and in 12 years when my oldest turns 18 i dont even want to imagine the nonsense that's going to be going on then. 
seriously let's rewind the clocks and go back to the 60s.

union minister m.j. akbar, a former editor, is the first politician to be named in the flood of sexual allegations propping from the #metoo movement wave.
.

text:
the forest had a maw so gaping
sabertoothed branches ravenous
never to enter mothers would beg
it is forbidden fathers would warn.
was she foolish, was she willful
to be so deep in under dark boughs?
rebel or careless, so much to blame?
living in that wolf shadow a ghostling
scorned and cursed in hushed breaths
accusers beholding her moving bones
cannot grasp what happened there
they cannot accept the evidence 
that proves the forest came to her.
.
.
poem "the forest" by t.stark 
artwork by @rivuletpaper .
.

text: today marks one year since @milano_alyssa tweeted the #metoo hashtag for the first time after rose mcgowan (and many other women) accused hollywood producer harey weinstein of sexual assault. the spread of the hashtag all over the planet through fall last year and well into the spring of 2018 showed the world that sexual assault and abuse is far more common than the public wants to admit, and not only for women; the hashtag helped people of all genders step forward  after having spent ages feeling trapped and alone in a situation that affects so many of us on a daily basis. the fight is not over, and you are not alone in it. #metoo #believewomen #believesurvivors

text:
#metoointhegym

we want to hear your stories about unwanted sexual attention at the gym. 1 in 3 women have a bad story to tell. the gym should be a safe space for women, yet oftentimes we feel uncomfortable. did the guy next to you 'eye-grope' you? did a personal trainer touch you inappropriately? whatever it may be, we want to hear your stories. don't worry, you'll stay anonymous. drop us a dm to share your experience with us. 
if you have any tips or recommendations on how to prevent uncomfortable situations at the gym, what to do if you find yourself in such a situation or anything else, don't hesitate to let us know.

#african
lewinsky affair not an abuse of power, says hillary clinton file photo of monica lewinsky hillary clinton has said her husband billâ€™s affair with former white house internÂ monica lewinsky was not an abuse of power and he was right to not resign from the us presidency in the wake of the scandal. the two-decades-old episode has come under renewed scrutiny in the #metoo era, with critics questioning whether the power imbalance between a sitting president and an intern made it impossible for the relationship to be considered consensual. some, like new york senator kirsten gillibrand, have said that clinton should have stepped down after he was impeached by a republican-controlled house in late 1998 for lying about the affair. but speaking on cbs news on sunday, former presidential candidate and secretary of state hillary clinton said she disagreed. â€œabsolutely not,â€ she replied when asked whether her husband should have resigned. pressed on whether the relationship was an abuse of power, clinton said: â€œno, noâ€ and noted that lewinsky, who was 22-years-old at the time, â€œwas an adult.â€ â€œthere was an investigation and it, as i believe, came out in the right place,â€ she added. in 1999, the senate held a month-long trial of president clinton that ultimately fell well short of the two-thirds majority required to convict and remove him from office. lewinsky, for her part, long maintained the affair was consensual, but in an essay published in vanity fair earlier this year wrote she had begun to re-evaluate that view. bill clinton has also been accused by several other women of sexual misconduct in cases going back to the 1970s, prompting a reckoning of his place in history by democrats in light of the #metoo and timeâ€™s up movements. afp  the post lewinsky affair not an abuse of power, says hillary clinton appeared first on channels television. source: channelstv

similarly, traditional engineering and oil & gas companies had a lowÂ incidence of sexual harassment complaints being filed. these sectors employ 30 percent or less women as a portion of their total workforce

text:
on account of the #metoo tide taking over our country (india), drowning some in shame while lifting up the voices of the once unheard, i am going to share my opinion and story too. as much as i love putting my thoughts and emotions into words, i know it is my responsibility to even talk/write about my experiences related to #metoo too. and so i will.
.

i will be sharing through posts and there are 6 parts to it, in total.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

@regran_ed from @christianah_akindolie -  child  abuse is indeed a silent epidemic. 
1 in 3 girls and 1 in 6 boys are abused before age 18. 90% of predators are family members, friends of the family, domestic staff, teachers, coach etc. they are well-known & trusted by you and i.

at this free event, you will learn: - the dynamics of child abuse
- signs and effects of child abuse
- how to identify an abuser
- proven strategies for prevention
- effects of domestic violence on  children. - you will also hear real life stories from survivors.
-have access to educative materials -the first 50 people will get a book titled - "unspoken family secrets written by christianah akindolie, a renowned child safety advocate.

this event is for parents, women groups, religious leaders, teachers, survivors, youth leaders etc

over a 100 people have registered already. we need a 100 more. seats are fast filling up!

text:
i found myself waking up every night all because you filled me with fright
i know i could try once again tonight but i rather just fight it off
you scare me even though i know you cant get inside the house or call 
but i still feel you miles and miles away
so i cant sleep at night 
all i feel is the fright 
that you put into me every night 
no i cant sleep at night all i feel is the fright that you set in my blood lines
you act like you gon come to my town, i'm look round like where you now, you thinkin i'll be by myself but you're funny because i'll have someone else, here to make me feel pretty , somebody here to keep me safe instead of driving me insane
you make me feel this pain all through my brain, causing me these hallucinations from sleep deprivation 
so
so i cant sleep at night 
all i feel is the fright 
that you put in my blood lines
no i cant sleep at night all i feel is the fright that you put in my blood lines. - kinsey shea

text:
heute vor 3jahren kamen bei 37+6 unsere zwillinge per kaiserschnitt zur welt.

das foto hat mein mann bereits ende der 35.ssw gemacht,es zeigt wieviel mein bauch leisten musste und leider habe ich kein finales bild,allerdings ist der bauch zum schluss noch etwas gewachsen. lange habe ich dieses bild niemanden gezeigt.

heute feiern wir den 3.geburtstag unserer zwillinge,bis hier hin war es ein langer weg.

text:
pride of place in the @vamuseum  medieval and renaissance galleries is vincenzo de rossi's sculpture of the rape of proserpina. visitors coo over the dynamism of bronze rendered into flesh, the ripple of perfectly formed renaissance anatomy in the god pluto and his victim proserpina - who was abducted to be his sex slave in the underworld while her mother wept. her gaze calls out for mercy and her outstretched arm says no as well as effectively displaying her graceful body. the dark god's face is focused on his depraved intentions and her toes curl in fear. where once i would have talked about this work as an example of skill in material exploitation or of an italian renaissance interest in the stories of the classical world, i now feel uncomfortable about how we collectively overlook the dark sexual violence it narrates and i'm not quite sure what we should do about it.
#rapeculture #rapeinarthistory #metoo #renaissance #sculpture #plutoandproserpina #isbeautyanexcuse?

text:
so yesterday i was traveling to boisar. a place near virar, mumbai. i was going to my grandmother's place.
i witnessed a thing which i would like to share.

i was travelling in a rickshaw from railway station to the destination where i wanted to reach,
i was sitting in the front with 3 other guys including the driver,

back part of the rickshaw was forcefully filled with 4 people, while the actual maximum capacity was of 3 people.

there were 2 teen girls on the left side, followed by one lady of almost 30-35 years of age, and then there was an old man aged between 55-60.

i am making myself clear here itself that i am not supporting or opposing any person or gender here, just read it till the end.

eventually like every other place in our country the roads were not in a good condition obviously,

because of which we were getting many jerks on the roads, eventually during one such big pot hole, the old man may have accidentally touched the lady which happened involuntarily ( i guessed so, i maybe wrong too) and if i guessed it wrong then he got what he deserved but also look at the other point of view.

so the lady immediately started shouting "how dare you touch me, you bloody cheap pervert" 
to which the man immediately apologized and said it was because of the pothole and not intentional.

she told the driver to stop and started yelling at the man that she knows what he was upto, every men is the same.

she told the man to come out to which the man refused and was also apologizing continuously that it wasn't intentional it was by mistake.

and suddenly 3-4 men appeared all of a sudden, they didn't arrive they just appeared all of a sudden which happens every time when there is a fight in our country because there are large number of unemployed people in our country and this is the only entertainment source they have.

the lady got inside and slapped the man and then the other 3-4 men took the matter in their hands "without even knowing what happened" they just took him out and started beating the hell out of him, he was already bald and a bit weak as his age was almost 55-60 and they were just beating him vigorously just because the lady slapped him. â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸

text:
recently, tanushree dutta's allegations against veteran actor nana patekar took the bollywood industry by storm and a lot of people have started calling out their abusers on social media. 
in the wake of this, dangal actor aamir khan had found out that a person he was supposed to work with in future, was called out in the #metoo movement. so, the actor has cut off all ties with the above mentioned person, and also cancelled the project. 
following this, he gave a statement regarding the me too issue, and clarified his stance. he said: "as creative people we have been committed to foregrounding and finding solutions to social issues, and at aamir khan productions we have always had a zero-tolerance policy towards sexual misconduct and predatory behaviour of any kind. we strongly condemn any act of sexual harassment, and equally we condemn any and all false accusations in such cases.

two weeks ago, when traumatic #metoo stories began emerging, it was brought to our attention that someone we were about to begin work with has been accused of sexual misconduct. upon enquiry we found that this particular case is subjudice, and that the legal process is in motion.

we are not an investigative agency, nor are we in any position to pass judgement on anyone - that is for the police and judiciary to do. so, without casting any aspersions on anyone involved in this case, and without coming to any conclusions about these specific allegations, we have decided to step away from this film.

we do not want our action to reflect in any manner on the people involved in this case.

we believe that this is an opportunity for the film industry to introspect and take concrete steps towards change. for far too long women have faced the brunt of sexual exploitation. it has to stop. in this regard we are committed to doing any and everything to make our film industry a safe and happy one to work in." - kiran rao and aamir khan

text:
today is #mentalhealthawarenessday and #mentalhealthawarenessweek .
.
.
you may be thinking "what has this image got to do with mental health", well let me tell you! .
.
.
i was diagnosed with complex ptsd  after things that happened when i was 14 to 15 years old in school.. nhs told me there was no cure, no one qualified to help and a good chance i wouldn't make it to 30.. i was put on around 18 tablets tablets a day and i reached around 26 tablets a day when i was 21 years old, this made things worse and i was no longer me, just an angry zombie..., i was put on countless talking therapies none of this helped
.

then one day, i decided enough was enough i was going to save myself, i came off all 26 tablets a day cold turkey (do not recommend) turned my back on mainstream medicine, and flew to india to learn holistic psychology!  thankfully my parents already were qualified and own @crystalmoonemporium so know all things holistic so they helped me a lot
.
.
.
i felt better, but still felt the c-ptsd was in control not me
.
.
.
i then found out about ayahuasca, i heard how people with the same condition as me had found a way to control it
.
.
.

i flew to mallorca in july to sit with ayahuasca and that is when my life started to change, for good and what i thought at the time bad as i was in tune with every living thing (including plants and animals)
.
.
.
i went back to mallorca last week for a woman's healing retreat and by gosh did i heal!! the c-ptsd will always be with me, but it is my tool now, i control it!! so yes, a yurt does await, your own personal key to unlock the way to healing, just like ayahuasca did for me <3 .
.
.
i wish one day to live in a world that proactively teaches mental health and tries its best to heal rather than try to make money from it and belittle it!!
.
.
.
.
.

#mystory #life #india #mallorca #ptsd #ayahuasca #healing #healed #mentalhealth #mentalhealthwarrior #mentalhealthawareness #dontbescared #love #lovealways #lovevibes #key #journey #yurt #plant #medicine #plantmedicine #share #storytime #myjourney #travel #learn #warrior #metoo

huge congratulations to 2018 #nobelpeaceprize laureate, nadia murad, who has been a brave and powerful voice for survivors of human trafficking and victims of sexual violence. in 2014, at the age of 19, murad was kidnapped in iraq, held hostage, and constantly subjected to sexual violence. after escaping 3 months of captivity, she started seeking justice for victims everywhere, telling her story to the world time and again, even though that meant reliving horrific memories of abuse and suffering. thank you nadia, for your courage to speak up and seek justice, not just for yourself, but for all survivors of sexual violence.

text:
when i was a freshman in highschool a guy was annoyed by me so he humped me and grinded himself on my side when i was talking to my friends. i felt disgusted and shocked, it was like a barrier i had kept around myself for safety had been broken. like i was being touched not in that specific area of the body but all around me. like worms had crawled everywhere. 
so i roughly pushed him off me until he fell to the ground. sometimes i wish i beat him up instead but i was too much in a state of shock to do so.i told my teachers and parents but all they did was laugh and dismiss me.
"you shouldve liked it, you're gay right?"
"i mean...he did so many things for you so i guess you can excuse that small mistake right?"
it was one of the first times i was sexually assaulted.

text:
i honestly don't understand the people of this world. they say that they support women, they say that if and when a women is sexually harassed or raped or has gone through something of that sort then they should come forward and talk about it, to create awareness and to change. yet when they get what they ask for and women are now finding the courage to step forward, they are being accused of their allegations being fake and they're not being believed. why do people ask for change if they can't support it when it's happening. the saddest thing for me is that they're so many women who have come forward but because the people being accused are in a higher position of power/fame/or have money, people automatically stay quiet and don't support them. imagine how many more women have been sexually abused by people of power but it's been kept hidden because of their social status and fame. and automatically because this person is well known people are like 'oh he would never do something like that' etc... but how do you know. it's so easy to put forward a fake persona or act a certain way on camera, it's not hard at all. so many people take advantage of their position whether it's someone who is in a high place of authority lawfully, someone who has a higher place in society because they appear to be more religious or pious, or someone who has money and is famous. it's easy for these people to do something like this and get away with it because they know they can brush it under the rug and if it does come out their status in society or in the world will sway people towards them rather then against them. the last thing i have to say is... when someone say's they've been raped or sexually abused/assaulted you should believe them. it takes a lot of courage and bravery to come out about something so traumatizing so do not call that person a liar, let them have their justice, if we really want change in the world and we want to get rid of people who rape and abuse and we want a better world for our brothers and sisters and children then we have to do something about it, speak about it..... @2ukhts || @herfatalmuse

text: (part 2) itâ€™s an unspoken truth, if you are a fit, disciplined, regular gym goer with a good sense of fitness knowledge, you are probably not the most ideal profitable member profile for a gym with a commercial focus, as you may not take most of their key revenue generating services like personal training, etc. but you will be attending the gym almost everyday which relatively increases users on the gym floor at a given time , as compared to an over weight member who is not regular, has no idea about fitness & nutrition would be an ideal member profile giving high revenues & low daily maintenance cost. i have one important thumb rule for everyone to guide you to make the right decision while choosing a gym or a fitness alternative, get fitness literate! educate yourself about your own health, speak to other reliable trainers you know. donâ€™t you find it strange if you are a banker, marketeer, researcher, etc. an ace in your profession but you donâ€™t have enough knowledge about your own body, health, food, fitness requirements? once you have enough knowledge, check around for gyms, fitness studios that donâ€™t aggressively try to promote personal training, other services, but give sufficient attention to training all their members. i hear a lot of folks saying oh we have a gym in the office or iâ€™m a gym member in 2 clubs or i know everything about fitness & health. fitness has to be visible! if you donâ€™t see noticeable results in your health, stamina, overall fitness inside out, over a consistent period of time you may have all the amenities & insights but none of these are benefiting you, itâ€™s just a superficial feel good factor & a waste of your hard earned money! #metoo ! ğŸ’ªğŸ»ğŸ˜ŠğŸ‘ŠğŸ» #strengthtraining #weighttraining #fitnessmotivation #fitnessmodel @pumaindia #pumahybrid #calvinklein #burberry #porsche #zara #beastmode #fit #crossfit #healthyeating #fitnessgirl #fitgirlsguide

text: 071018 part1. let me tell you something i have kept quiet about for more than four years that finally reached an end. i left home on october 7 on a sunday afternoon after i asked my husband to give me some money to buy food because he hasnt bought food for the past 2 months. he wanted me to pay for my own food. mind you, my husband and soon to be ex husband had always been hostile. i got into healthy food and workout because i wanted to prove myself and god that it is possible to change by giving a person so much love. last week was the final blow. as we were arguing i told him im leaving that day if he doesnt buy food. i explained that i am losing my milk because of stress from our fights & not being able to eat if the neighbor's mom doesnt give me food. he was defiant. so i told him i am taking sofia with me. he grabbed the baby and i grabbed her back. he said "i will call the police if you leave with her". i said go ahead! he gave her to me and i went upstairs. i put sofia on the bed and took my large stroller bag. i entered sofia's room & told his mom who's now using my baby's room: "excuse me i have to take your luggage out 'cause im taking my stuff". the arrogant old woman looked at me and said "are you talking to me?" with her sarcastic face. i said yes, im taking my stuff so im taking out your bag first. she smirked at me! i took my luggage in front of my room and his mom pretended not to know what was happening asked me what happened in a very sarcastic manner. i told her what happened because im stupid thinking she was sympathizing with me. then the old woman said "i dont believe you!" and "altha, i'm not scared of the police. my grandfather was a police officer so you cant scare me". i said sure im not either. and im not the one who said i will call the police its your son! im leaving with sofia today because he doesnt want to buy food. the evil woman said: "you know you cant do that, you cant take her with you" with her very evil face. i said of course i can. she was saying many things as i locked the door. i called cps and the police. i didnt know that time that my husband left the house. his mother stayed behind... to be continued...

text:
we all recognise the importance of continuing to strive towards equality in the workplace. however, there is still a long way to go. in light of the frightening information being shared through campaigns such as #metoo and #timesup we need to give serious consideration to how we better support the safety, wellbeing and growth of women in all workplaces.

created in response to feedback from thousands of female leaders, accord provides a simple, cost effective way for organisations to increase trust and engagement, create connections across various levels and provide a structured environment to nurture and develop female talent. importantly, accord represents an agreement between organisations and their female staff to work together to create a safer, more supportive and more equitable working environment.â€‹ expressions of interest for the accord program are now open- we highly recommend you check it out if you value your female staff members. https://www.wla.edu.au/accord.html #femaleempowerment #womenandwork #womeninbusiness #womenleaders #femaleleaders #safeworkplaces #supportwomen #valuewomen #womenandleadershipaustralia

text:
it was one year ago today the revolution weâ€™ve been working for finally started. women started speaking about the years of harassment, sexual violence and fear. millions of women. millions of stories and experiences. we broke the culture of silence. a culture of keeping it quiet because we could loose our job, reputation, relationships and social status. weâ€™ve kept quiet because weâ€™ve been taught to blame ourselves. because of the fear of more violence. and the fear of not being believed. but no more. youâ€™ll never have the convenience of our silence again.

and it all started with one woman: tarana burke. she started the movement #metoo and one year ago alyssa milano released the wildfire with her tweet about the sexual violence she experienced. women came together from all over the world to demand an end to the war of mens violence against women. the war that have been going on for centuries, in all levels of society, all around the world. womenâ€™s bodies are being butchered, just because we are women. we are raped by our colleagues and classmates. we are murdered by the people we love. we are oppressed, humiliated, over-sexualized and attacked in our everyday life. but no more. youâ€™ll never be able to hide behind fake excuses saying you didnâ€™t know.
.
we know that you know now. so every leader, politician, boss, company, school or organization that doesnâ€™t take action to prevent inequality and sexual harassment takes a stand against women. because you know better. so do you want to be a part of the solution - or a part of the problem?
.
men who are allies: act! learn more about toxic masculinity, speak with your friends about being a man today, and speak up: womenâ€™s right is not a womenâ€™s issue! itâ€™s about humans right and thatâ€™s everyoneâ€™s business. solidarity equals action!
.
women and non-binary: you are not alone. it wasnâ€™t your fault. and i believe you. and we can demand more: equal pay, new laws, education about sexual violence, report to the police, dump a partner that isnâ€™t treating you right, make your school take action against bullies and so on.
.
and remember that we stand together.
we are never backing down.
we will never again be silent.

tarana burke, the woman who founded the #metoo movement

how was the #metoo started?

tarana burke originally coined the phrase me too on 'my space' while working at just be inc., a nonprofit company that was founded by her in 2003.
she started a project focusing on the overall well-being of young women of colour.
the life-changing movement began when burke was talking to a girl who revealed that her motherâ€™s boyfriend had been sexually abusing her.
she didn't know what to say, she just said 'me too'.
burke was left searching for the right words to help empathise with the countless women and young girls who have disclosed their experiences to her.
burke has shared the message with survivors everywhere: youâ€™re not alone. this happened to me too.
she was able to create a storm with just 500 twitter followers.
the movement became an internet sensation when actress alyssa milano stumbled upon this phrase and tweeted this.

text:
ğŸ™my daughter forwarded this meassage to me :
as the #metoo movement takes people by storm, i can't help but think of those incredible men in my life - in whose presence i feel safe... i feel secure... i feel protected... i feel loved.
sometimes, we tend to lose sight of what is right...too important, what is happening and i fully support it. and yet, just a small attempt - to remember... #wetoo have met some of the most amazing gentle, tender, beautiful humans in the world... many of who happen to be men!
i dont want the millions of young girls reading #metoo posts only seeing men in one light, fearing if they too will become a #metoo someday. let's talk as much of what is right too! what say? to my driver, to my cook, to my male friends, to my husband, to my father and to many father like figures in my life... irrespective of some in your gender letting you down, i want to tell you, i still believe in you. #metoo  please share this message if you agree - and want the world to know some bad does not negate the good.

hot news
kangana ranaut tantang karan johar dan shabana azmi, yang bungkam soal gerakan usut tuntas pelecehan seksual, me too ğŸ˜‰

di tengah gerakan #metoo yang sedang berkembang, aktris kangana ranaut telah memberikan tuduhan kepada sutradara film queen, vikas bahl melakukan pelanggaran dan bahkan meluncurkan serangan baru terhadap hrithik roshan. 
bintang film manikarnika: queen of jhansi kini telah memanggil dan menantang pembuat film karan johar karena mempertahankan keheningan atas isu yang sedang membara itu. jatuh pada sutradara film ae dil hai mushkil, kangana mengatakan kepada media dalam sebuah wawancara, â€œdimana orang-orang seperti karan johar dan shabana azmi ? orang-orang ini juga harus keluar untuk memberikan suara atas gerakan #metoo juga.â€. sungguh ganas perkataan kangana. â€œkaran johar memiliki pandangan tentang penampilan tubuh seorang bintang. dia bahkan menulis tweet sepuluh kali tentang itu. bagaimana dengan ini? inilah identitas mereka. ini roti dan mentega mereka. ketika industri film sedang mengalami perubahan yang penting, dimana mereka?â€, tambah kangana geram.

aktris film rangoon ini lebih lanjut mengkritik konsep acara yang dipandu karan, koffee with karan, mengatakan, â€œsaya melihat beberapa promo yang telah mereka luncurkan untuk talkshow ini. lagi-lagi pembicaraan sembrono yang sama sedang berlangsung. yang ini tidur dengan yang ini, yang satu dengan yang itu. membuat gadis terlihat seperti boneka barbie, itu tidak harus dilakukan. dan mengapa pria yang mengubah wanita seperti pakaian sedang dimuliakan? apakah ada seorang wanita yang telah dimuliakan seperti ituâ€. kangana melanjutkan dengan menambahkan, â€œkita perlu mempromosikan pria yang memproyeksikan menjadi satu pria-wanita. seseorang yang berpura-pura menjadi casanova, kita tidak perlu memuliakan itu. budaya dimana anda berkencan dengan seorang wanita selama 10 tahun dan meninggalkannya seperti mengganti pakaian. saya tidak menghakimi siapa pun, mereka semua teman saya dan mereka cantikâ€. kangana dikenal karena tidak pernah menepis kata-kata dan selalu... text:
warning : if you are a *pseudo* feminist then don't read further.

dear #metoo
i have a question for you, will you answer me? please?

actually i was just wondering that can males too use this hashtag? and if they'll do then will society believe them too? if they'll come up with their issues without any proof, will they be listened?

i'm asking all these questions because i believe that everyone has a story to tell.
it's not compulsory that shit happens only with one gender. sometimes it can be a boy too.

just imagine a boy posting that he was raped. yes, there will be some people who'll believe him and will help him too but the majority of comments will go like : 1.
2.
3.
..
..
do i seriously need to mention some? hey come on, i know you already got me.

see i'm not against you, i know things start for a good and so did you. many hidden stories came in the picture. many genuine *humans* got justice. but the society in which we live, these things spread like a cancer. people just exaggerate everything. yeah, i agree it's not easy to use these things for publicity but believe me there are obviously some people who do it for the same.

most importantly, girls just keep their point in words, mind me just in words and we as a society believe them, why? because they are girls. this social media can ruin anyone's life/career and that too in a single day. don't you think that a girl can use this against a boy whom she hates, maybe who rejected her. we as a society say no means no, so same goes for the boys too, maybe there can be a boy who said no to a girl and to take revenge she can use you mr. #metoo, can't she?

everyone suffers! and everyone includes all the genders. i'm not disagreeing that girls don't suffer but with that i agree that boys suffer too. if a boy gains enough guts to raise his voice then not even all other boys will support him, agree?

p.s. - it wasn't intended to hurt anyone's feelings and sentiments, i respect you girls but with that i respect boys too or precisely you can say i respect humans.
-------------------------------------------

text:
the #metoo stories while real are disturbing. as a women who is 30 now, i know that every single women has stories of being harassed in some way or the other - the degree, the circumstance is all that varies.
.
but, while the #metoo stories scare me, given that i need to raise my kannama in this ugliness, it also gives me hope.
.
the world that was unsafe for women to go about their daily routine, is now unsafe for men too in a different way - if you think you can pass a comment on a co-worker and get away with it, think again.
.
the hope again is that the way certain people, brands, companies are being penalized is more permanent, than a temporary one. i've heard enough folks tell me that "the ceo is stepping down till the dust settles".
.
if i've to prepare kannama on how to deal and be safe in this ugly world, than have a safer place at the end of all this, what would be the point really? .
on a separate but connected note, i've also noticed mom influencer profiles being attacked, hacked in the last few days - this is harrassment in the new age, isn't it? i'm speaking specifically about @aweekinlife and @hashtagdisha. the digital world that is enabling women to speak up, is also being used to shut them down?
.
i've been very wary of social media myself. i've never shared a picture of my daughter cos of the fear of how that maybe used. i've never shared too many specifics about our life cos i don't want to risk our privacy or worse, safety.
.
i started this profile to chronicle my journey with my daughter, for me to relive these moments when she is older!
.
but, i also happen to have found a lovely community here and have connected with like-minded individuals - @ammatoday, @andhowdoyoudo, @the.quixotic.quaintrelle and many more!
.
i've also found a bunch of fellow parents who inspire me in the way they raise their kids -@mommy_stories, @artventuretales, @littlefingersatwork, @timesofamma and more.
.
and to think they do all this in the fear that maybe attacked if they speak their own mind?
.
here's hoping for a better world where truly my kannama can feel like she is on top of the world, and flying!

text:
from the archive (aka loft) evidence of my short-lived â€˜careerâ€™ as a print baron with my mate jon westbrook.
the launch (and only) issue of â€˜it?â€™ magazine, dated september 1996, featured the divine comedy as the cover star. 
the interview was by jon pictures by yours truly.
we were all over that new-fangled interweb, of course. câ€™mon, it was 1996!
not to mention the little chat we had with the mighty rocket from the crypt.
we even had album reviews!
it appears that we loved the new offerings from the boo radleys and suede. kula shaker not so much.
other top features included the, um, hilarious â€˜bazaarâ€™ spoof showbiz news section. 
our big, completely untrue, story was the blossoming romance between liam gallagher and david bowie. 
weirdly, the one about blurâ€™s damon albarn actually came true, sort of.
we also had a very 2018-esque cartoon about cannabis, in 1996!
but, amongst all this â€˜90s indie pop frippery, the piece that really jumps out is @corinnasilk speaking out about men who stared and shouted at her in the street.
remember, this was amidst the burgeoning â€˜lads magâ€™ phenomenon and some two decades before #metooâ .

text:
i stated plenty times before, automation will wipe over 2.5 billions jobs in less than 10 years.  this is why i recommend current students going to college for robotics and mechatronics engineering. most other degrees and careers will be wiped out. it will be like the industrial revolution.

as with any piece of technology, the first models are expensive, but the more saturated it gets the cheaper the price gets. some examples are the television, ipads, smart phones and plenty more. a 4k television used to be $4000+ when it first came out, now you can get a 55" 4k tv for $300 on black friday.

these robots will be expensive when they first come out, but eventually they will become cheaper to purchase than one construction workers salary. what do you think a company is going to do when he can get one for $30,000. gonna say the hell with paying benefits, salaries and lawsuits and buy one robot and deal with the repairs by hiring some robotic engineers to fix it.

@regran_ed from @lex_j_432hz -  ever notice how we are being subjected to robots? slowly but surely, bigger and more intelligent robots are being deployed for us to buy and use.

we are being conditioned to think it is normal to have robots all over the place, at work and in our houses. for example, we have vacuum cleaners that operate on their own while we relax and do nothing. we think nothing is wrong because we are conditioned to accept this new way of society.

as the years go on, slightly more advanced robots will be released for public use until eventually we have actual human-sized robots inside our houses doing all sorts of things  from doing our laundry, making food and washing dishes.
ğŸ‘€
donâ€™t accept this technology. donâ€™t buy it either. take a look at all the small robots that are available for the public to use and do not buy them! they want to condition us. itâ€™s the transhumanism age.

text:
this account was an impulsive thing but i figured itâ€™s time. 
this account is basically my journey to being a healthier person. 
whether itâ€™s on the outside or in the inside, i want to feel healthier in general. 
let me introduce myself if you donâ€™t already know about me. 
my name is cait. i am 21 years old. i am a wife to an amazing husband, david. we got married this year on cinco de mayo #tacolove. i am mostly a stay at home wife. i got diagnosed with bipolar at the age of 17. before then, was 4 years of hardships and pain (both physical and emotional). i started gaining weight at the age of 11 during my 6th grade summer. i gained about 80ish pounds in 10 years. about every year, i seem to gain 5-10lbs. i recently lost 20lbs back in april. i gained all 20 back plus a couple pounds but luckily still fit my 20lbs ago clothes. my dream is to be a youtuber and share my journey. i have started a blog, which you can see the link in my bio. the blog basically talks about some of the struggles and things i have gone through out the years. i have always wanted to be a motivational speaker ever since i was a kid. i am also a #metoo survivor. 
my goal for this is to maybe help someone out whether theyâ€™re having a bad day or maybe just need some inspiration.

somethings i have dealt with that i may talk about in a later blog or video are:
self harm
suicide attempts
suicidal thoughts
anxiety/anxiety attacks
panic attacks
sexual assault
self esteem issues
infidelity

thank you for joining me on this journey towards healthier living!

my heart is broken for each fellow individual who has experienced sexual violence, and was not only forced to relive their trauma these past few weeks, but was also nationally shamed, silenced, discredited, mocked and devalued by the state and its supporters.  iâ€™m deeply saddened and enraged, but not surprised. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

our stories are powerful and important. if you want to share yours, please do, we will listen and believe you. if you donâ€™t want to share, donâ€™t feel shame or obligation. your autonomy, safety and wellness is priority.  either way know you are valued, respected, loved and credible. if anyone needs an ear i am here to listenâ¤ï¸ â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

we pledge to never victim blame. we will listen, honor and protect victims.

but thereâ€™s also another conversation that has resurfaced here. 
most of us are overdue for taking a long, hard look at the multitude of ways racism and sexism feed off of each other, and the ways that we, as white women, are complicit in each. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

white women: we have got to do better. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

white women protect the patriarchy because weâ€™ve believed that proximity = power. and to some extent thatâ€™s correct. there are privileges afforded as a reward for upholding the status quo.  but this comes at enormous cost to ourselves, to women everywhere, to black people, poor people, people of color, lgbtq people and every marginalized group. for decades white women have shortsightedly chosen white supremacy over a global, inclusive womenâ€™s liberation â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

white male supremacy seeks endless power and resources for itself with disregard to the needs, rights and demands of everyone else whom they exploit. white supremacy, patriarchy and capitalism are near inextricable bedfellows that represent the core cause of human suffering. â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
â €â €â €â €â €â €â € â €

white women: the patriarchy will collapse, but it will do so much more quickly if you stop supporting it. white women voted in trump, supported roy moore, and barely disapproved of kavanaugh. this is crazy. divest now. learn to identify internalized misogyny and your own racism, and shut it down. keep read

text:
there was a time when no one listened to her squeal
no one really cared, a stream of acid made here beautiful face peel.

there was a time when they tried to pull her down
when they teased and lusted her in a night gown.

there was a time when her birth was considered a bad omen
in the mother's womb itself her breath was frozen.

there was a time when her lifeless body was found in the drain,
how could she ever express her pain?

a change is brimming up right now
and we are reaping what we all in the past sow.

a shimmer of hope over the coming days
let all those past cultures have to be set ablaze.

never let there someone to say like this again
"there was a time when.." with deep disdain.!!! #metoo#doodlingvoice âœ ğŸ”Š#engineerbyprofessionğŸ‘»#artistbyheartğŸ’“#firstpostoninstagramğŸ’™

text:
an open letter by priya malik ( @priyasometimes )
.
this is to tell you that while it is courageous to speak about your harassment experiences because everyone is listening right now, it is equally courageous to not speak because you are not ready yet, because you are not comfortable talking about it, because you donâ€™t think it is the right time for you; stay brave. because although it requires a lot of gumption to speak up, it requires the exact amount of courage to stay silent simply because you are not ready yet.
.
you may not have a recorded phone call or a series of screenshots or a gmail chat proof or a string of emails and text messages, you may wish to stay anonymous or show your name, you may wish to not talk about it on twitter but talk about it with your friends, but none of this absolves from the fact that you are living with your truth every minute of the day and by god, that takes strength, courage, resilience and a great degree of self awareness.
.
#metoo #metooindia #metoomovement #priyamalik #shethepeople

text:
i cant really say this about just one thing because it's subjective.

if i use love as the example, then yeah i know what it's like to learn a really hard lesson.

loving someone so much you lose yourself, and feeling like you'll never have that love again.

and i never did. i now have something so much better. but if i didnt really learn that lesson about what i needed to give up in order to get what i wanted, what i deserved, best believe history would have repeated. i would have had my heart broken all over jext time round.

this lesson is one of many. every single thing that happens to us, is teaching us a lesson.

dont wallow, dont think "why me". think "why" fullstop. what is the lesson here?

the answers are all around us you just need to look.

text: my take on # metoo . the #movement against #sexual #harassment has exploded in india's entertainment and news industries .#sexualassault is unacceptable. i feel it is an awakening and a reminder that we as a society cannot be complacent. we both have feminine n masculine power, shiva n the shakti.  we need feminine power for creation n nurturing. masculine energy  is action oriented, giving and visionary . at some point  in past society started getting dominated by agressive masculine energies and feminine became weaker and victimised. to have harmony masculine and feminine has to be in balance .then only creation is possible. the women who have joined this movement have chosen to come out of the darkness they are like the phoenix that will rise from the ashes of their shame,guilt , suppression and inhibitions . there is a lot of impact on the mental health of the victim. there is a sense of powerlessness feeling guity or dirty depression and anxiety. overcoming sexual assault takes lot of commitment and time.  but once you overcome the negative into positive, your life will change forever. you will be stronger than before and undoubtedly a better version  of your own self.  power is in the now. it is important to free yourself of the #suppressed emotions especially #anger.self compassion , self forgiveness, healings, meditation and internalisation are some of the tools that can be used for healing this #trauma.it helps a lot to have a trained #counsellor .#selfco@passion #meditation #internalisation #healing #forgiveness #power #now #lifecoachpeyush #mentalhealthsupport #depression #anxiety #lifecoachdelhincr #messagefromtheuniverse #tellmewhatyouthink  #sexualharrasmentatwork#anxietyrelief #lifecoachinnoida #changeyourmindset  #awareness #depressionquotes #metoomovement #metoo

text:
on a *new new new* project for me! i've been working (really hard) on my first proper menu consulting for @cafekothi in jaipur. whaaaa. it's been hard to contain my excitement because i've always wanted to try this, and cafe kothi is exactly my vibe ~ fresh, local, seasonal with a focus on health too. foods and flavours are one of my favourite things, and i spend half my time dreaming about them and wanting to try new ideas. so yeah, i'm pretty thrilled with this opportunity to explore everything that it entails - trials and tweaks, tastings and changes, plating, colours, flavours, gosh. (plus, pretty ceramics).
.
we're working on the new winter menu for cafe kothi. i've never worked in a kitchen before, so it's been so much learning every.single.day. kitchens are fairly exhausting work too (props to all of you who do it each day). we're doing dessert today, and i couldn't have asked for a better monday. trying a chocolate-tahini tart. (i've been pretty obsessed with tahini - it works really well in cocoa-date bliss balls, so i can't wait to try this tart). ğŸ¤ğŸ½
.
eeks, so much love @inses and @abhishekhonawar. thanks for the vote of confidence and letting me work on this with you. ğŸ¤¸ğŸ»â€â™€ï¸ (photo ~ @hetalchhabria â™¥ï¸).
.
oh, wearing @generationmixx. this new #genderequal tee is the softest, most comfortable. plus, i love the colours.
.
p.s. ~ completely unrelated, but while it's important to keep up with #metoo and have all those conversations to inform your opinions and decisions, it can be emotionally exhausting. plus we've all got to work, be productive and participate in our regular lives. it's completely okay to take a break from it, and go back when you're ready. i took a few days off last week, where i didn't check twitter and it was good for me. #hugs
.
.
.

text:
just another day in the city.
-- today, someone told me that #metoo is getting out of hand. 
it made me realize how oblivious the world is to the struggles of half the population.

so, in sharing as many of our stories as i can on one platform, i'm hoping people see that these aren't isolated incidents. this is the reality for 50% of us!

do send in your stories - anonymously or otherwise - the world needs to know.

text:
there is an essential difference between powerlessness and weaknesses. so when i asked my friend what image does your brain present when we utter the word weak, the reply came: all the women who tolerate abuse from their partners to protect their children. they are perceived as weak and incapable, but they are true survivors.

to all the women out there who lack financial/social means and support to walk out of an abusive relationship and are tolerating it just because of your children. you are not weak! you are a strong human. 
and to all the women who came out of abusive relationships without knowing where the next meal will come from or where you will go for shelter, you are courageous.

#inkrober2018 prompt #weak

text:
last month cristiano ronaldo was accused of rape. this is not the first time this has happened to the juventus striker and one of the most successful, popular and richest athletes in the world. kathryn mayorga filed a civil lawsuit at a nevada district court accusing cristiano ronaldo of rape back in 2009. she eventually dropped these charges after she was paid 375,000 dollars to be quiet nine years ago because she did not want her name to become public. ronaldo along with other big time soccer players like neymar and messi are occasionally in trouble with the law over tax evasion, so they are not new to having issues with the law. this accusation of ronaldo by mayorga has been brushed under the rug because of how big of an athlete ronaldo is. he paid her to be quiet and said this was fake news. this story is still forming and mayorga has filed a lawsuit saying that ronaldo had no right to make this information public. this story is just one example of corruption in major sports and how the victim can sometimes be the one who looks like the enemy. #ecstorytellers #ronaldo #juventus #soccer #sexualassualt #equality #metoo

text:
when i am fortunate enough to interact with people who validate my trauma, which is many of you, i am often told how strong i am. while it gives me some sense of hope, i can't help but feel deceitful because i have been barely keeping it together. but yet, i often preach about empowerment and being kind to yourself.
there are lies we have to tell because we need to believe them ourselves. 
i get asked lots of questions by people who are wondering if it ever gets better and i say "of course it gets better." how could i bear to tell them that i don't know the answers and the limits of their pain? 
my honest answer to you all when you ask if it gets better over time is:
i have had to convince myself of the time and distance between then and now so many thousands of times that surely it has done something, right? or that it gets better until it doesn't. it gets better until there's a split moment where you see someone who looks like him and a sharp pang runs through the center of my body. i feel sick to my stomach. and i have to remind myself over and over that he can't hurt me anymore.
when i close my eyes i only sometimes see his cold eyes staring back, yes, that's an improvements. 
sometimes the reality after it getting better over time is not what you are hoping for. you have to relish the small returns to independence. the nights without the nightmares. the days without the stomach churning anxiety. the panic attack that you got under control. the fact that you only cried once today. it's all been small victories for me. 
that's the truth.

text:
fact: the distribution of powers is skewed in the favour of the patriarch. 
musing: the conversation for too long has been about bringing attention to basic rights, but itâ€™s also important to remind ourselves of the beauty in a coven of women. through this collection, i wanted to bring into focus to the solidarity that gets created in the face of resistance.

i felt female when my grandmother taught me how to make mango pickle while reciting monsoon hymns. i felt female when my mother showed me how to drape a saaree. i felt female when my sister told me someone she knew violated her. i felt it when my aunt told me that empowered women are feared. .

#maharani is about touching base with femininity, whatever that might mean for you. itâ€™s about looking at the archetype of the female, rejecting what didnâ€™t work and retaining what did. #metoo

text:
as a survivor of sexual abuse at the age of 5 and rape at 14, i would like to salute all those that have spoken up and plan on doing so. i know it is very difficult to do it because i have been there and it took me many years to be able to talk about it. it takes immense amount of courage to share this with the world. itâ€™s even harder when you tell those that are close to you and they are supposed to protect you, yet they do nothing. i have been there too and it hurts like hell. but i want these survivors to know it is truly liberating and completely worth it. do not let the nonbelievers stop you. this is your truth. do not ever be afraid to speak your truth. do not let this opportunity pass you. this is a moment that has been long overdue for all of us. this is your chance to be heard and finally obtain justice. i believe you.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #ibelieveyou #somyali #speakup #shoutitout #iamwithyou #survivors #truth #takeastand #staystrong #wecandoit #justice #longoverdue #pakistan #india #bollywood

text: in the last few days i've been an ear to bend for two sexual assault victims and i have been sexually assaulted by a man who continually thinks it's okay to touch me or rub up against me inappropriately. im tired of being silent. putting your hands on a female who isn't your spouse or girlfriend in a sexual manner is wrong!  when are men going to fucking get this?! i've been sexually assaulted more times than i can count in my life, i've stood by and let it happen, paralyzed and unsure of how to handle it, blaming myself. i've come to the conclusion that its not my fault. it's their fault.  for men who are unsure of what sexual assault is....let me educate you....its ranges from inappropriately touching of a body part to rape. men are disgusting degenerates who think it's okay to do this kind of shit to women. if you are a man and reading this, second guessing if you have ever done this or made a woman feel like this, odds are, you have. i'm no longer staying silent, i'm no longer going to be paralyzed when i'm touched inappropriately, i'm no longer going to blame myself and i know now how to handle it. we as women need to start standing up for ourselves and stop letting men continue to get away with this. i'm standing up for myself and fighting back, i hope you will too. #sexualassaultawareness #standingup #speakingout #metoo

text:
one of the emotionally painful situations for me with meeting new people or even people that i know is that people don't listen.

i went to a writers group the other day and it was just myself and this other woman and the teacher and the woman asked me a question about myself. -------------------------------------------------------------------
i answered her & there was somebody coming out of an office and she got distracted and started looking there and didn't hear my answer. ----------------------------------------------------------------------------i asked her, "did you hear my answer?" and she said no and i just said, "that's good to know." --------------------------------------------------------------------------- i can't control other people....but it's very painful for me that people in this society at least a certain amount of people.....not all, don't listen to another person, don't hear the other person..... are not aware. --------------------------------------------------------------------there is such a lack of awareness in the society. it's does happen lot of times, makes it really hard for me to bond with other people as an introvert. --------------------------------------------------------------------------
i have decided to really take care of myself and be willing to remove myself from these situations where people don't listen or hear me. my challenge is, how to keep my heart open despite this. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- ğŸ’•ğŸ’šğŸ’™ğŸ’—ğŸ’“ğŸ’•ğŸ’™ğŸ’šğŸ’›ğŸ’›ğŸ’›ğŸ’šğŸ’™ğŸ˜˜ğŸ’•ğŸ’“ğŸ’•ğŸ’“ #femalestandupcomics #losangeles #haynes_charli #california #standupcomics #charlihaynesnotyourtypicalanorexicskinnybitchyoutube  #oregon #laughteryoga #laughter #losangeles #overcominganxiety #santamonica #hilarious #california #losangelesstandupcomics #spiritual #spirituality #spiritualcomedy #humor #spirituality #metoo #metoomovement #feminism #selfcare #feminismforeverybody #femaleempowerment #funny #peacefulmindpeacefullife #peaceful

iâ€™ve struggled with disordered eating for 20 years. 
i always find myself minimizing this because, how can you have an eating disorder and be plus-size. i would roll my eyes when girls said they had anorexia assuming they just wanted attention, so i figured since i wasnâ€™t telling everyone about it then it wasnâ€™t a problem. 
but the thing is, i wear that problem every single day. you can literally see my disorder. i remember as a teenager being told how my voracious appetite for candy would catch up to me one day. i vividly remember eating 3 candy bars everyday during drivers ed. if thatâ€™s not disordered, idk what is. 
itâ€™s taken me a long time to come to terms with it. i have to tell myself everyday, sometimes every hour, that i do like being healthy!

i actually feel better and have better control over every area in my life when iâ€™m staying on top of my nutrition. but once one plate drops it all goes to hell. and thatâ€™s where accountability has to come. 
having someone who iâ€™m checking in with daily, if not multiple times a day has made such a huge difference!! and knowing that thereâ€™s someone there that if i fall off the wagon and eat two pounds of cinnamon bears in one day, i can turn to them...itâ€™s priceless. 
and thatâ€™s what iâ€™m trying to give out in return. iâ€™ve found an incredible nutrition program that not only allows me to eat and enjoy it but also lose weight at the same time. so iâ€™ve got a simple routine, accountability i can trust, and workouts available when it fits with my schedule ğŸ™ŒğŸ¼. if youâ€™ve got emotional eating problems, overheating issues, and feel completely lost and donâ€™t know how you can make a change, iâ€™d love to talk more and see if i have a solution for you! 
because babe, youâ€™ve probably tried every program under the sun, but i know this can work for anyone! you are worth the work it takes to dig out, and i promise, itâ€™s way easier than you think! iâ€™m rooting for you!!!

text:
i am not a nice girl. 
i guess this piece is done. i began this project all the way back in february but set it aside for several months when i lost steam. recent weeks have inspired me to finish it. 
if we get angry, we are overbearing bitches. if we cry or scream, we are hysterical or overemotional. our expression of ourselves, our reaction to the world around us and how others treat our bodies is tightly controlled by the expectation to always be "nice, pleasant and accommodating." meanwhile, men's anger is rewarded as "passionate." well, i am not a nice girl and i don't give a fuck about what you think. be mad. be very mad.

text:
the first part of this is pretty clear. the only clarifying it might need is that i don't really think the question is about whether we "believe." rather, i think it is more about whether we care.

the second half comes from being a teacher and a therapist. my stance on the changes that are needed now comes from the fact that i believe men are capable of more. i believe in men, means i believe they can do better. and, i believe it is harmful to them to do harm, and so it is actually a compassion to demand them to stop (it is not a compassion to condone it). believing in men is actually an important counter to the rhetoric that "men are biologically wired [to rape, to look down your shirt, to whatever else....]" and that there is nothing they can do about it. this rhetoricâ€“carried by many womenâ€“furthers the belief that men cannot control themselves, are less smart, strong or self-aware than women, and do not have the same capacity for emotions or respect. and i just don't buy it! i think way more highly of them. people who carry this rhetoric often fail to notice that it is the same logic behind blaming the victim. 
the second part of "i believe in men" creates the space for ones who have made a mistake to atone, see the error, and become an ally. i do think it is important that those who have misused power face consequences, have losses and be distanced or restrained in any way needed to keep others safe. but there must also be a path to heal and to create something new. 
don't use the "i believe in men" to go to the good-guy-storyline either. my saying this does not collude with the men who get defensive around the current situation saying "most guys are good." i believe in men also applies to being strong enough to not be defensive. 
let's just add one more thing to this though. maybe for a while, men could listen rather than explain. maybe they could let women take the lead of the healing of their own wounds. men: you are strong enough to stop. you are strong enough to listen. #metoo #therapy #menstherapy #somaticpsychology #psychology #ibelievewomen #healing #emotions #teachers #patriarchy #men #atonement #apologize #repair #humans

â €

â €
while addressing a crowd in early october in southaven, miss., trump mimicked ford's failure to remember details from the night during the summer of 1982 when she claims kavanaugh groped her and tried to remove her clothes. kavanaugh has denied her accusations.â €

â €
"i had one beer and that's the only thing i remember," trump said at the time, imitating ford's testimony. â €
